divs: sighting detailsi had to take my dog out to do his thing. i noticed this extra bright star like object with pulsating, white\blue with a notable color changes especialy, like a band about the mid section. i have no idea how far it was from where i watched it at an altitude about 30 deg high, west to east. i noticed the star like object in the direction e by ne 'moving', mostly horozintaly and what looked like circles, over the area above the central cascade mtn's three sister's. the intensity of the light varied. i used my pourch rail to view this thing from a fixed point. it also seemed to dip and circle, but it would move far enough that it sometimes would go behind the tree limbs. all together i watched it for about 15 minutes.
Summary: Bright, pulsating, light 'white,blue w/ amber to red, moving around.
trends: There have been no other sightings in Goshen
